5. What is the difference between the String methods indexOf( ) and lastIndexOf( )?
	indexOf() provides the first instance of the searched substring. lastIndexOf provides the last matching substring.

6. Since all strings are objects of type String, show how you can call the length( ) and charAt( )
methods on this string literal: "I like Java".

String temp = "I like Java";
System.out.println("The length of the string \"I like Java\" is: " + temp.length() + " and the character at index 0 is: " temp.charAt(0));

